def complete(self, replacement: Optional[str]) -> str:
    if replacement is None:
        return self.raw_source[self.start:self.end]
    
    start_line, end_line = self.get_line_pos(self.raw_source)
    indent = ' ' * (len(self.raw_source[:self.start]) - self.raw_source[:self.start].rfind('\n') - 1)
    
    lines = replacement.split('\n')
    indented_lines = [indent + line if i > 0 else line for i, line in enumerate(lines)]
    completed = '\n'.join(indented_lines)
    
    return f"{self.raw_source[:self.start]}{completed}{self.raw_source[self.end:]}"
